-- Colombian Stocks: Isagen SA, Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp.
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-04-23T20:49:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/colombian-stocks-isagen-sa-pacific-rubiales-energy-corp-.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.7 percent to 14,915.56, while the
Colcap Index decreased 0.5 percent to 1,746.29.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN)  , a Colombian state-run power
producer, advanced 2 percent to 2,370 pesos. Investors may be
speculating that the stock will be added to the MSCI Emerging
Markets Index in the next rebalancing, Juan Camilo Martinez, an
analyst at Medellin-based brokerage Bolsa y Renta, said in a
telephone interview.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, slumped 2.4
percent to 50,340 pesos. Oil decreased in New York as
manufacturing contracted in China and the euro area, bolstering
concern fuel consumption will decline.  To contact the reporter on this story:
